<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install (Mac)</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Download and unzip the Mac build</li>
    <li>Drag <strong>ClaudeUsageMonitor.app</strong> to your Applications folder</li>
    <li>Right-click the app and choose <strong>Open</strong> (required on first launch)</li>
    <li>Log in to claude.ai if prompted</li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install (Windows)</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Download and unzip the Windows build</li>
    <li>Right-click <strong>Install.ps1</strong> and choose <strong>Run with PowerShell</strong><br>
      <small>(or from PowerShell: <code>powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\Install.ps1</code>)</small></li>
    <li>The installer copies files to <code>%LocalAppData%\Programs\ClaudeUsageMonitor</code>, adds a Start Menu shortcut, enables auto-start, and launches the app</li>
    <li>Log in to claude.ai if prompted. Look for the % in the system tray (click the ^ near the clock if hidden, then drag the icon out to pin it)</li>
  </ol>
  <p><small>Portable use: just double-click <code>ClaudeUsageMonitor.exe</code> from the unzipped folder — no installation. Requires Windows 10 1809+ (x64) and the Microsoft Edge WebView2 Runtime (pre-installed on Windows 11).</small></p>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Features</summary>
  <ul class="tool-shortcuts">
    <li><strong>Menu bar / tray icon</strong> Session % with color coding; switches to daily budget remaining when session is low</li>
    <li><strong>Usage meters</strong> Session (5hr), Weekly, Sonnet, and Extra Usage ($)</li>
    <li><strong>Daily budget</strong> Remaining weekly % divided across days until reset</li>
    <li><strong>Pace tracking</strong> Compares usage vs time of day and projects end-of-day total</li>
    <li><strong>History chart</strong> Bar chart of daily usage for the past week</li>
    <li><strong>Notifications</strong> Alerts at configurable session and weekly thresholds, daily budget exceeded, extra usage, session reset, and back-on-pace</li>
    <li><strong>Cross-platform sync</strong> Mac and Windows share the same daily baseline via a Dropbox-synced file — numbers match across machines</li>
    <li><strong>Global hotkey</strong> Alt+Ctrl+C to toggle the panel (Windows); configurable menu on Mac</li>
    <li><strong>Launch at login</strong> Configurable in Settings</li>
  </ul>
</details>
